## 3. SIMULCAST STRATEGY

### Architecture

```
OBS (AERO X16)
  └─► Restream.io RTMP (Europe - Frankfurt)
        ├─► YouTube Live (@EIWerner)
        └─► Twitch (@eiwerner)
```

Restream is cloud-based: OBS encodes once, sends one RTMP stream, Restream duplicates server-side. This means simulcasting adds **zero additional upload bandwidth or encoding load** on the local machine.

### Confirmed OBS Stream Settings (March 31, 2026)

| Setting | Value | Why |
|---|---|---|
| **Service** | Restream.io | — |
| **Server** | Europe - Frankfurt | Autodetect routes badly on this connection (C1) |
| **Video Encoder** | NVIDIA NVENC H.264 | Hardware encode — minimal GPU gaming impact |
| **Rate Control** | Constant Bitrate (CBR) | Required for stable RTMP |
| **Bitrate** | 4500 kbps | Safe ceiling for 8–10 Mbps actual upload (C2) |
| **Keyframe Interval** | 2 seconds | Restream hard requirement (C3) |
| **Preset** | P5: Slow (Good Quality) | — |
| **Output Resolution** | 1920×1080 | Matches ZenScreen native |

### Title Management

**Restream is the single source of truth for stream titles.** Titles set in YouTube Studio or Twitch dashboard do not reliably propagate when streaming through Restream. Always use `app.restream.io` → Update Titles before going live (C4).

### Chat Monitoring

| Platform | Method | URL |
|---|---|---|
| **Twitch** | Popout tab on laptop | `twitch.tv/popout/eiwerner/chat` |
| **YouTube** | YouTube Studio app on iPad | Live stream → chat panel |

OBS's native YouTube Chat dock is unavailable when routing through Restream (OBS is not directly authenticated to YouTube in this path). iPad is the permanent solution.

