## 4. RECORDING STRATEGY

### Architecture

Three simultaneous outputs run alongside the Restream stream:

| Output | Method | Auto-starts? | Encoder |
|---|---|---|---|
| **ISO: Camera** | Source Record filter on camera source | ✓ Yes | NVENC H.264 |
| **ISO: Gameplay** | Source Record filter on gameplay source | ✓ Yes | NVENC H.264 |
| **Full canvas composite** | OBS built-in recorder | ✗ Manual | x264 |

**NVENC session count:**
```
1 × Restream stream          (NVENC H.264, 4500 kbps)
1 × Camera ISO               (NVENC H.264, CQP 18)
1 × Gameplay ISO             (NVENC H.264, CQP 18)
─────────────────────────────────────────────────
Total NVENC: 3    ← within RTX 5070 Laptop limits

Full canvas uses x264 intentionally — preserves NVENC headroom
```

> All recordings write locally to SanDisk SSD — zero upload bandwidth impact (C18).

### Plugin: Source Record

```
Plugin      Source Record by Exeldro
Version     v0.4.8+ required for OBS 31.x
Install     obsproject.com/forum/resources/source-record.1285/
Rating      3.68/5 — known: OBS freeze on exit (mitigated v0.4.8), audio crackling workaround required
Fallback    Branch Output (hanatyan) — 4.57/5, more stable, fewer features
```

### ISO Camera Recording Config

Target source: `TheCatCamera` (Elgato Facecam MK.2 physical device)

```
Filter type         Source Record (Effect Filter)
Record Mode         Streaming       ← auto-starts with OBS Start Streaming
Output Path         D:\StreamSourceFiles\Recordings\Camera\
File Format         MKV             ← crash-safe; remux to MP4 post-stream
Encoder             NVENC H.264     ← NOT "NVENC new" — broken (C15)
Rate Control        CQP
CQP Value           18              ← raise to 20–22 to reduce file size if needed
Different Audio     Enabled
Audio Source        Mic track       ← workaround for audio crackling bug
```

> Source Record captures at the raw source native resolution — Facecam MK.2 = 1080p regardless of canvas transforms.

### ISO Gameplay Recording Config

Target source: Window Capture of WoW (Borderless Windowed) — never Game Capture (C10)

```
Filter type         Source Record (Effect Filter)
Record Mode         Streaming
Output Path         D:\StreamSourceFiles\Recordings\Gameplay\
File Format         MKV
Encoder             NVENC H.264
Rate Control        CQP
CQP Value           18
Different Audio     Enabled
Audio Source        Game audio track
```

### Full Canvas Recording Config

OBS → Settings → Output → Recording tab (Advanced mode):

```
Recording Format    MKV
Encoder             x264            ← intentional — avoids NVENC session pressure
Rate Control        CRF
CRF Value           18
Preset              veryfast        ← drop to ultrafast if CPU spikes
Audio Tracks        1, 2            ← track 1: mix; track 2: mic isolated
Recording Path      D:\StreamSourceFiles\Recordings\FullCanvas\
File Naming         %CCYY-%MM-%DD_%hh-%mm-%ss_FullCanvas
```

> Does NOT auto-start with streaming (C14). Must be started manually — see checklist below.

### Recording Folder Structure

```
D:\StreamSourceFiles\
└── Recordings\
    ├── Camera\         ← ISO camera (Source Record)
    ├── Gameplay\       ← ISO gameplay (Source Record)
    └── FullCanvas\     ← Full composite (OBS built-in)
```

### Vertical / Portrait Crops (Shorts / TikTok)

Source Record ignores canvas transforms — do NOT apply it directly to the camera source for vertical output. Instead:

1. Create scene: `CameraVertical_1080x1920`
2. Right-click scene → Scene Settings → 1080×1920
3. Add camera source → crop for portrait framing
4. Apply Source Record filter to this scene, not the raw source

