## 6. ISSUES ENCOUNTERED — FULL HISTORY

### Issue Log Format

Each entry: **Root cause → Symptom → Fix → Status**

---

### [I-01] WoW crash on transmog / Warband UI
- **Root cause:** WoW DirectX compatibility issue
- **Symptom:** Game crash on specific UI interactions
- **Fix:** Add `-d3d11` to Battle.net Additional Command Line Arguments
- **Status:** ✅ Fixed Mar 17

---

### [I-02] OBS Game Capture causing GPU crashes
- **Root cause:** Game Capture hooks into WoW's DirectX pipeline — conflicts with GPU under load
- **Symptom:** GPU instability, crashes during WoW streams
- **Fix:** Switch OBS to Window Capture; set WoW to Borderless Windowed mode
- **Status:** ✅ Fixed Mar 17

---

### [I-03] Daily BSODs — `nvlddmkm.sys_Blackwell` (MEMORY_MANAGEMENT 0x1A)
- **Root cause:** Corrupt or incompatible NVIDIA driver on Blackwell GPU
- **Symptom:** BSOD `nvlddmkm.sys` — daily, unpredictable
- **Fix:** DDU clean uninstall → fresh install NVIDIA driver 595.79 WHQL
- **Status:** ✅ Fixed Mar 17

---

### [I-04] OBS resolution mismatch — black bars / cropping on Display Capture
- **Root cause:** Laptop display is 2560×1600 (16:10); OBS canvas is 1920×1080 (16:9)
- **Symptom:** Display Capture of laptop screen produces black bars or cropped image in OBS
- **Fix:** Use ZenScreen MB16ACV (1920×1080 native) as dedicated broadcast display. OBS Display Capture pointed at ZenScreen — native resolution match, no bars.
- **Workaround for laptop screen content:** Window Capture of specific app (e.g., Notion resized to 1600×900 via PowerToys)
- **Status:** ✅ Fixed Mar 17

---

### [I-05] GiMATE ECO mode disabling dGPU
- **Root cause:** ECO mode routes all GPU output through integrated AMD Radeon only
- **Symptom:** OBS and games using integrated GPU instead of RTX 5070 — poor performance
- **Fix:** GiMATE → set to Optimus mode permanently. Never use ECO mode.
- **Status:** ✅ Fixed Mar 17

---

### [I-06] Wrong stream titles on YouTube and Twitch at launch
- **Root cause:** Titles set directly in YouTube Studio and Twitch dashboard instead of through Restream
- **Symptom:** Both platforms showed wrong/stale titles when stream went live
- **Fix:** Titles must always be set via Restream → Update Titles. Restream is the single source of truth for titles when simulcasting. Never set titles on destination platforms directly (C4).
- **Status:** ✅ Fixed Mar 31

---

### [I-07] OBS disconnecting immediately on first stream attempt
- **Root cause:** Two settings had never been corrected for Restream: bitrate at 9000 kbps (too high for Restream Standard and apartment upload), keyframe interval at 0/auto (Restream requires exactly 2 seconds)
- **Symptom:** OBS connecting and disconnecting repeatedly; Twitch showing UNSTABLE
- **Fix:**
  - Output → Bitrate → 6000 kbps (then further to 4500)
  - Output → Keyframe Interval → 2 seconds
- **Status:** ✅ Fixed Mar 31

---

### [I-08] Severe dropped frames at 65%+ even after bitrate reduction
- **Root cause:** OBS Server set to Autodetect — routing to a poorly performing server. Cannot be changed mid-stream.
- **Symptom:** 65%+ dropped frames, OBS cycling connecting/disconnecting, speed test showing actual upload only 8.4 Mbps
- **Fix:**
  1. Stop stream
  2. OBS Settings → Stream → Server → Europe - Frankfurt (never Autodetect)
  3. Drop bitrate to 4500 kbps (confirmed safe ceiling for 8–10 Mbps actual upload)
  4. Restart stream
- **Key constraint established:** Never use Autodetect. Never change server mid-stream. (C1, C2, C8)
- **Status:** ✅ Fixed Mar 31

---

### [I-09] Dropped frames counter still climbing after Frankfurt fix — false alarm
- **Root cause:** OBS dropped frames counter is cumulative per session — it carries all frames from earlier failed attempts in the same OBS session
- **Symptom:** Counter appeared to keep rising after switching to Frankfurt + 4500 kbps — caused alarm about whether the fix worked
- **Fix:** Full computer restart for a clean session. After restart with Frankfurt + 4500 kbps + keyframe 2s, both YouTube and Twitch showed EXCELLENT within 2 minutes.
- **Key constraint established:** Always restart OBS (or full machine) for a clean dropped frames read when testing (C7)
- **Status:** ✅ Fixed Mar 31

---

### [I-10] Camera feed dying when Camera Hub was quit
- **Root cause:** OBS camera source was pointed at "Elgato Virtual Camera" — a software layer that Camera Hub runs. When Camera Hub is quit, Virtual Camera shuts down with it, killing the OBS camera feed.
- **Symptom:** After reboot, Camera Hub auto-launched on startup. Quitting it killed the OBS camera feed entirely.
- **Fix:**
  1. In OBS: double-click camera source → change Device from "Elgato Virtual Camera" → "Elgato Facecam MK.2" (physical device)
  2. In Camera Hub: open → verify settings → hit Save (writes to camera's onboard flash memory) → X out → quit fully from system tray
  3. Camera Hub does not need to run during streams. Settings persist to camera hardware.
- **Camera Hub pre-stream ritual:** Open → verify → Save → X → system tray quit. This order matters (C5, C6).
- **Status:** ✅ Fixed Mar 31

