## 8. TROUBLESHOOTING REFERENCE

| Symptom | Likely cause | Fix |
|---|---|---|
| Wrong titles on YouTube / Twitch | Set in platform dashboards instead of Restream | Restream → Update Titles — always (C4) |
| OBS disconnecting on stream start | Bitrate too high or keyframe not set | Bitrate → 4500; Keyframe → 2s (C2, C3) |
| Dropped frames 65%+ | Autodetect server routing to bad server | Stop stream → Frankfurt → restart (C1) |
| Dropped frames counter climbing after fix | Cumulative counter not reset | Stop stream → restart OBS or reboot (C7) |
| Camera feed dies when Camera Hub quits | OBS pointed at Virtual Camera, not physical | Set source to Elgato Facecam MK.2 (C5) |
| Choppy camera feed ~90 min into stream | Camera Hub running, causing memory leak | Quit Camera Hub fully via system tray (C6) |
| Black bars in OBS Display Capture | Laptop screen 16:10, OBS canvas 16:9 | Use ZenScreen as broadcast display (I-04) |
| WoW crash on transmog / Warband UI | DirectX compatibility | `-d3d11` in Battle.net CLI args (I-01) |
| GPU crashes during WoW stream | Game Capture hooking DX pipeline | Window Capture + Borderless Windowed (I-02, C10) |
| Source Record not recording | Record Mode wrong | Filter → Record Mode → Streaming |
| Audio crackling in ISO recording | Source Record audio bug | Enable Different Audio → select mic track explicitly |
| OBS freezes on exit | Source Record known bug | Force-close OBS; MKV recordings intact |
| NVENC error in Source Record | Session limit hit | Switch full canvas to x264; reduce ISO count |
| Full canvas recording not running | Forgot manual start | Start Recording after Start Streaming (C14) |
| Gameplay ISO black / empty | Game Capture used | Confirm Window Capture is the source (C10, C12) |

